commit 6822dd6fddf1632fbf4cbe5f19a904fe727da5e9
Author: 0x4D44 <martingdavidson@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 8 12:56:28 2026 +0100

    Wire DNN modules into codec pipeline behind dnn feature flag
    
    Connects the standalone DNN modules (LPCNet, FARGAN, PitchDNN) into
    the encoder/decoder pipeline, gated behind #[cfg(feature = "dnn")]:
    
    - Replace PitchDNN stub with real pitchdnn::PitchDnnState delegation
    - Add LPCNetPLCState to OpusDecoder with set_dnn_blob() for model loading
    - Wire SILK PLC: lpcnet.update() on good frames, lpcnet.conceal() on lost
    - Wire CELT PLC: FRAME_PLC_NEURAL with 16kHz->48kHz sinc resampler
    - Thread lpcnet through decode call chain via DnnPlcArg type alias
    - Add DRED FEC stub (fec_add/fec_clear wiring)
    
    Zero behavior change when feature is disabled — all existing tests pass
    unchanged. When enabled without loaded weights, falls through to
    classical PLC preserving bit-exactness.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

